collectFeesAndRecordVolume(address,uint2.details: Requires prior token approval. Reverts if amount is zero or token address is invalid

params._asset: The asset involved in the trade
params._feeAmount: The amount of fees to collect
params._tradeSize: The size of trade in USD for volume tracking

returns._0: An array of all tracked asset addresses
The cumulative trade volume for the asset

params.index: The index in the tracked assets set

returns._0: The asset address at the given index
The count of assets with recorded trade volume

initialize(address,address,uint256).details: Can only be called once due to initializer modifier. The fee must be less than FEE_PRECISION

params._owner: The address that will own the contract
params._strataxFee: The initial Stratax fee in basis points

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

proxiableUUID().details: Implementation of the ERC-1822 {proxiableUUID} function. This returns the storage slot used by the implementation. It is used to validate the implementation's compatibility when performing an upgrade. IMPORTANT: A proxy pointing at a proxiable contract should not be considered proxiable itself, because this risks bricking a proxy that upgrades to it, by delegating to itself until out of gas. Thus it is critical that this function revert if invoked through a proxy. This is guaranteed by the `notDelegated` modifier.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby disabling any functionality that is only available to the owner.

setFee(uint256).details: Only callable by owner. New fee must be less than FEE_PRECISION

params._newFee: The new fee value in basis points

setStrataxPositionNft(address).details: Only callable by owner. Required for position validation

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

upgradeToAndCall(address,bytes).details: Upgrade the implementation of the proxy to `newImplementation`, and subsequently execute the function call encoded in `data`. Calls {_authorizeUpgrade}. Emits an {Upgraded} event.

withdrawFees(address).details: Only callable by owner. Transfers entire balance to the owner

params._token: The ERC20 token address to withdraw

withdrawFees(address,uint256).details: Only callable by owner. Allows partial withdrawal of accumulated fees

params._token: The ERC20 token address to withdraw

assetTradeVolume(address).notice: Mapping of asset address to cumulative trade volume

collectFeesAndRecordVolume(address,uint2.notice: Collects fees by transferring tokens from sender to this contract

getAllAssetVolumes().notice: Gets trade volume for all tracked assets

getAssetTradeVolume(address).notice: Gets the trade volume for a specific asset

getTrackedAssetAt(uint256).notice: Gets a tracked asset address by index

getTrackedAssetsCount().notice: Gets the total number of tracked assets

strataxFee().notice: Stratax fee in basis points e.g., 5 for 0.05%

withdrawFees(address).notice: Withdraws all accumulated fees for a specific token

withdrawFees(address,uint256).notice: Withdraws a specific amount of fees for a token
